3 (4) "Foreign national" means any of the following:
4 (a) An individual who is not a citizen of the United States.
5 (b) A government, or subdivision, of a foreign country or a
6 municipality of a foreign country.
7 (c) A foreign political party.
8 (d) Any entity, including, but not limited to, a partnership,
9 association, corporation, organization, or other combination of
10 persons, that is organized under the laws of, or has its principal
11 place of business in, a foreign country.
12 (5) (4) "Fund raising event" means an event such as a dinner,
13 reception, testimonial, rally, auction, or similar affair through
14 which contributions are solicited or received by purchase of a
15 ticket, payment of an attendance fee, making a donation, or
16 purchase of goods or services.
17 (6) (5) "Gift" means a payment, subscription, advance,
18 forbearance, rendering, or deposit of money, services, or anything
19 of value, unless consideration of equal or greater value is given
20 in exchange.
21 (7) (6) "Honorarium" means a payment of money to a person
