3 Sec. 15. (1) The secretary of state shall do all of the
4 following:
5 (a) Make available through his or her the secretary of state's
6 offices, and furnish to county clerks, appropriate forms,
7 instructions, and manuals required by this act.
8 (b) Develop a filing, coding, and cross-indexing system for
9 the filing of required reports and statements consistent with this
10 act, and supervise the implementation of the filing systems by the
11 clerks of the counties.
12 (c) Receive all statements and reports required by this act to
13 be filed with the secretary of state.
14 (d) Prepare forms, instructions, and manuals required under
15 this act.
16 (e) Promulgate rules and issue declaratory rulings to
17 implement this act in accordance with the administrative procedures
18 act of 1969, 1969 PA 306, MCL 24.201 to 24.328.
19 (f) Upon On receipt of a written request and the required
20 filing, waive payment of a late filing fee if the request for the
21 waiver is based on good cause and accompanied by adequate
22 documentation. One or more of the following reasons constitute good
23 cause for a late filing fee waiver:
24 (i) The incapacitating physical illness, hospitalization,
25 accident involvement, death, or incapacitation for medical reasons
26 of a person an individual required to file, a person an individual
27 whose participation is essential to the preparation of the
28 statement or report, or a member of the immediate family of these
29 persons.individuals.
