1 (ii) Other unique, unintentional factors beyond the filer's
2 control not stemming from a negligent act or nonaction so that a
3 reasonably prudent person would excuse the filing on a temporary
4 basis. These factors include the loss or unavailability of records
5 due to a fire, flood, theft, or similar reason and difficulties
6 related to the transmission of the filing to the filing official,
7 such as exceptionally bad weather or strikes involving
