17 Sec. 24. (1) A committee shall file a statement of
18 organization with the filing officials designated in section 36 to
19 receive the committee's campaign statements. A committee shall file
20 a statement of organization within not later than 10 days after the
21 committee is formed. A filing official shall maintain a statement
22 of organization filed by a committee until 5 years after the
23 official date of the committee's dissolution. A person who fails to
24 file a statement of organization required by this subsection shall
25 pay a late filing fee of $10.00 for each business day the statement
26 remains not filed in violation of this subsection. The late filing
27 fee must not exceed $300.00. A person who violates this subsection
28 by failing to file for more than 30 days after a statement of
29 organization is required to be filed is guilty of a misdemeanor
THS H02963'25 (H-1) ikse7g

