5 (c) The total amount of bundled contributions delivered to
6 that candidate committee during the reporting period and during the
7 election cycle.
8 (7) (6) For a reporting period in which a bundled contribution
9 is received, a candidate committee of a candidate for statewide
10 elective office shall report to the secretary of state, on a form
11 provided by the secretary of state, all of the following
12 information, as applicable, about each contribution delivered as
13 part of a bundled contribution received in the reporting period and
14 about all bundled contributions received by that candidate
15 committee:
16 (a) The amount of each contribution, the date it was received
17 by the candidate committee, and the name of the bundling committee
18 that delivered the contribution.
19 (b) Each contributor's name and address and, for each
20 contribution exceeding $100.00, the contributor's occupation,
21 employer, and principal place of business.
22 (c) The total amount of bundled contributions received by that
23 candidate committee during the reporting period and during the
24 election cycle.
25 (8) (7) For a reporting period in which a connected
26 organization of a separate segregated fund makes a payment for a
27 prize or 1 or more items authorized under section 55(8), the
28 separate segregated fund shall report all of the following, as
29 applicable:
THS H02963'25 (H-1) ikse7g

21
1 (a) The amount of any payment of costs for a prize, the value
2 of the prize, the amount raised by the prize, and the amount, if
3 any, reimbursed to the connected organization by the separate
4 segregated fund for the prize.
5 (b) The amount per item of any payment of costs for items to
6 be sold or offered in return for a contribution as part of
7 fundraising fund-raising activities for the separate segregated
8 fund, the amount per item that each item is offered at or offered
9 for sale at, the value of each item, the aggregate amount paid for
10 those items, and the amount, if any, reimbursed to the connected
11 organization by the separate segregated fund for any items. If 1 or
12 more of the same items are sold or offered in return for a
13 contribution, a report by item type satisfies the reporting
14 requirement under this subdivision.
15 (9) (8) As used in subsection (7), (8), "value" means the
16 regular purchase price offered by the vendor from whom an item is
17 purchased, less any customary discount offered based on the number
18 of items purchased in the same transaction.
19 Sec. 34a. (1) A ballot question committee shall not knowingly
20 or willfully receive, solicit, or accept contributions from a
21 foreign national, whether directly or indirectly.
22 (2) After a ballot question committee receives a contribution,
23 the ballot question committee shall obtain from the donor an
24 affirmation that the donor is not a foreign national and has not
25 knowingly or willfully received, solicited, or accepted more than
26 $100,000.00 in aggregate from foreign nationals in the 4 years
27 immediately preceding the date of the contribution.
28 (3) A ballot question committee shall return a contribution
29 made by a person prohibited from making a contribution under
THS H02963'25 (H-1) ikse7g

22
1 subsection (1) not later than 30 business days after receiving the
2 contribution.
3 (4) A person that violates this section is subject to a civil
4 fine of not more than double the amount of the undisclosed
5 contribution.
6 Sec. 51. (1) A person, other than a committee, that makes an
7 independent expenditure, advocating the election or defeat of a
8 candidate or the qualification, passage, or defeat of a ballot
9 question, in an amount of $100.01 or more in a calendar year shall
10 file a report of the independent expenditure, within not later than
11 10 days after making that independent expenditure, with the clerk
12 of the county of residence of that person. If the independent
13 expenditure advocates the election or defeat of a candidate for
14 state elective office or for judicial office, or for the
15 qualification, passage, or defeat of a statewide ballot question,
16 or if the person making the independent expenditure is not a
17 resident of this state, the person shall file the report with the
18 secretary of state in lieu of filing with a clerk of a county. The
19 report required under this section must be made on an independent
20 expenditure report form provided by the secretary of state, include
21 the date of the expenditure, a brief description of the nature of
22 the expenditure, the amount, the name and address of the person to
23 whom it was paid, the name and address of the person filing the
24 report, together with the name, address, occupation, employer, and
25 principal place of business of each person that contributed $100.01
26 or more to the expenditure, and identify the candidate or ballot
27 question for or against which the independent expenditure was made.
28 If the independent expenditure advocates for the qualification,
29 passage, or defeat of a statewide ballot question, the report must
THS H02963'25 (H-1) ikse7g

23
1 include an affirmation that the person making the independent
2 expenditure has not knowingly or willfully accepted more than
3 $100,000.00 in aggregate from foreign nationals in the 4 years
4 immediately preceding the date the expenditure is made and that the
5 entity will not knowingly or willfully accept more than $100,000.00
6 in aggregate from foreign nationals through the date of the
7 election in which the ballot question will appear on the ballot.
8 The filing official receiving the report shall forward copies, as
9 required, to the appropriate filing officers as described in
10 section 36.
11 (2) If a person fails to file a report as required under this
12 section, that person shall pay a late filing fee. If the person has
13 made independent expenditures totaling less than $10,000.00, the
14 late filing fee is $25.00 for each business day the report remains
15 unfiled, but not to exceed $1,000.00. If the person has made
16 independent expenditures totaling $10,000.00 or more, the late
17 filing fee is $50.00 for each business day the report remains
18 unfiled, but not to exceed $5,000.00. A person that violates this
19 subsection by failing to file a report required under this section
20 for more than 30 days after the report is required to be filed is
21 guilty of a misdemeanor punishable by imprisonment for not more
22 than 90 days or a fine of not more than $1,000.00, or both.
23 Sec. 54. (1) Except as otherwise provided in this section and
24 section 55, and except with respect to loans made in the ordinary
25 course of business, a corporation, joint stock company, domestic
26 dependent sovereign, or labor organization shall not make a
27 contribution or expenditure or provide volunteer personal services
28 that are excluded from the definition of a contribution under
29 section 4(3)(a).
THS H02963'25 (H-1) ikse7g

24
1 (2) An officer, director, stockholder, attorney, agent, or any
2 other person acting for a labor organization, a domestic dependent
3 sovereign, or a corporation or joint stock company, whether
4 incorporated under the laws of this or any other state or foreign
5 country, except corporations formed for political purposes, shall
6 not make a contribution or expenditure or provide volunteer
7 personal services that are excluded from the definition of a
8 contribution under section 4(3)(a).
9 (3) A Except as otherwise provided in this section, a
10 corporation, joint stock company, domestic dependent sovereign, or
11 labor organization may make a contribution to a ballot question
12 committee or independent expenditure committee subject to this act.
13 A Except as otherwise provided in this section, a corporation,
14 joint stock company, domestic dependent sovereign, or labor
15 organization may make an independent expenditure in any amount
16 advocating for the election or defeat of a candidate, or the
17 qualification, passage, or defeat of a ballot question and does not
18 for this reason become a committee, unless it solicits or receives
19 contributions in excess of $500.00 for the purpose of making the
20 independent expenditure, but is subject to the independent
21 expenditure reporting requirements under section 51.
22 (4) A foreign national shall not do any of the following:
23 (a) Make a contribution, independent expenditure, or
24 expenditure to promote or defeat a ballot question or to qualify a
25 question for placement on the ballot.
26 (b) Solicit, directly or indirectly, a donation, contribution,
27 or expenditure by another person to promote or defeat a ballot
28 question or to qualify a question for placement on the ballot.
29 (c) Direct, dictate, control, or, directly or indirectly,
THS H02963'25 (H-1) ikse7g

25
1 participate in the decision-making process of a person to promote
2 or defeat a ballot question or to qualify a question for placement
3 on the ballot.
4 (5) A foreign national shall not make a contribution or
5 donation to any other person or entity with the express or implied
6 condition that the contribution or donation or any part of it be
7 used for any purpose prohibited under subsection (4).
8 (6) No individual, candidate, political party, committee, or
9 separate segregated fund shall, directly or indirectly through
10 another person or entity, knowingly do either of the following:
11 (a) Solicit, accept, or receive money from a foreign national
12 for any purpose prohibited under subsection (4).
13 (b) Make a contribution, expenditure, or independent
14 expenditure using money received from a foreign national for any
15 purpose prohibited under subsection (4).
16 (7) (4) A person that knowingly violates this section is
17 guilty of a felony punishable, if the person is an individual, by
18 imprisonment for not more than 3 years or a fine of not more than
19 $5,000.00, or both, or, if the person is not an individual, by a
20 fine of not more than $10,000.00.
